{#-
  NavigationMenu — Horizontal web-navigation menu. Wraps a Menubar in a
  <nav aria-label> landmark + signals identity via data-controller="navigation-menu".

  Per OQ-33 (sealed S2.3b opening): submenu items use Item with `as: 'a'
  href="..."` (real navigation destinations). aria-current="page" on the
  active nav item — consumer stamps per the current URL.

  Per OQ-30 architecture (sealed S2.3a): per-submenu DropdownMenus (each
  fully standalone) + a thin orchestrator (NavigationMenuController extends
  MenubarController verbatim — same mechanics, different semantic shell).

  Mega-menu (multi-column dropdown layout) is DEFERRED to Ring 3
  `pattern:Nav-MegaMenu`. S2.3b ships simple-column dropdowns only.

  Composes:
    - <nav aria-label="..."> landmark (per 13-a11y-baseline §13).
    - navigation-menu Stimulus controller (extends MenubarController).
    - N child DropdownMenu compounds (consumer-provided via {% block menus %}).
    - Submenu items: Item with `as: 'a' href`.

  Parameters:
    htmlId      (string, optional)  — auto-generated.
    label       (string, required)  — aria-label on the <nav> shell. Required
                                       per WCAG 4.1.2 when multiple navs exist;
                                       always-on is safe.
    labelledBy  (string, optional)  — aria-labelledby reference (overrides
                                       label if both present).
    className   (string, optional)  — extra classes on the <nav> shell.
    menubarLabel (string, optional) — aria-label on the inner menubar. Default
                                       is the same as `label` for chain consistency.

  Blocks:
    menus (required) — N DropdownMenu embeds. Each child's trigger MUST stamp
                       `data-navigation-menu-target="trigger"` AND
                       `data-popover-target="trigger"`. Submenu items SHOULD
                       use Item with `as: 'a' href="..."` (per OQ-33).

  Usage example (3 nav menus):

    {% embed '@theme/components/navigation-menu/navigation-menu.html.twig' with {
      label: 'Navigation principale'|trans,
    } %}
      {% block menus %}
        {% embed '@theme/components/dropdown-menu/dropdown-menu.html.twig' %}
          {% block trigger %}
            <button type="button" class="theme-menubar__trigger"
                    data-popover-target="trigger"
                    data-navigation-menu-target="trigger"
                    aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false">
              {{ 'Solutions'|trans }}
            </button>
          {% endblock %}
          {% block items %}
            {% include '@theme/components/item/item.html.twig' with {
              label: 'Pour les startups'|trans,
              as: 'a',
              href: '/solutions/startups',
              ariaCurrent: app.request.pathInfo == '/solutions/startups' ? 'page' : null,
            } %}
            ...
          {% endblock %}
        {% endembed %}
        {# ... more menus ... #}
      {% endblock %}
    {% endembed %}
-#}

{%- set htmlId       = htmlId       | default('theme-nav-menu-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set label        = label        | default(null) -%}
{%- set labelledBy   = labelledBy   | default(null) -%}
{%- set className    = className    | default('') -%}
{%- set menubarLabel = menubarLabel | default(label) -%}

{%- set _navClasses = ['theme-navigation-menu'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _navClasses = _navClasses | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- set _menubarClasses = ['theme-menubar'] -%}

<nav
  id="{{ htmlId }}"
  class="{{ _navClasses | join(' ') }}"
  {%- if label %} aria-label="{{ label }}"{% endif -%}
  {%- if labelledBy %} aria-labelledby="{{ labelledBy }}"{% endif -%}
>
  <div
    id="{{ htmlId }}-menubar"
    class="{{ _menubarClasses | join(' ') }}"
    data-controller="navigation-menu"
    data-action="keydown->navigation-menu#keydown"
    {%- if menubarLabel %} aria-label="{{ menubarLabel }}"{% endif -%}
  >
    {%- block menus -%}{%- endblock -%}
  </div>
</nav>
